==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Relator
<hw>Re*lat"or</hw> <pr>(r?-l?t"?r)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[ L.: cf. F.
<ets>relateur</ets>. See <er>Relate</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One
who relates; a relater.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧The several <xex>relators</xex> of
this history.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>Fuller.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>A private person at whose relation,
or in whose behalf, the attorney-general allows an information in the
nature of a <xex>quo warranto</xex> to be filed.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Relatrix</ent>⟦br⟧
